# MCP Factory — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
MCP Factory is a pipeline that takes a Windows DLL, discovers its exported functions
via static analysis, probes them with an LLM agent loop, and produces an enriched
schema + Python wrapper + verification report. Azure-hosted, FastAPI backend.

MVP target: 12/12 verified functions on contoso_cs.dll, then generalize to a folder of DLLs.

## Canonical Names (use these everywhere, never abbreviate)

### Core data structures
- `invocables` — list of invocable dicts (the function registry)
- `inv_map` — dict {name: invocable} (keyed registry)
- `_JOB_INVOCABLE_MAPS` — module-level registry in storage.py
- `vocab` / `ctx.vocab` — the cross-function semantic accumulator
- `findings` — list of per-function probe outcome dicts
- `ctx` — always an `ExploreContext` instance in the pipeline

### Sentinel / error codes
- `ctx.sentinels` — runtime sentinel table (int keys)
- `sentinel_calibration.json` — persisted sentinel table (hex-string keys, JSON limitation)
- `ctx.sentinel_catalog` — cross-probe evidence catalog (distinct from sentinels)
- `SENTINEL_DEFAULTS` — static defaults from sentinel_codes.py

### Session artifacts
- `session-meta.json` — contract artifact from cohesion.py
- `dashboard-row.json` — compact manifest for humans from collect_session.py
- `transition-index.json` — 21 cohesion transitions (T-01 through T-21)

### Job status
- Use `current_status` or `job_status`, never `_cur`, `_wucurrent`, `_gap_current`

## File Layout (api/pipeline/ — stage-based package)

### Shared infrastructure (api/)
- `main.py` — FastAPI app + job/explore endpoints
- `chat.py` — streaming agentic chat loop
- `executor.py` — DLL/CLI/GUI execution bridge
- `storage.py` — blob helpers
- `static_analysis.py` — binary static analysis (IAT, strings, sentinels)
- `cohesion.py` — T-01..T-21 transitions, session-meta, stage-index
- `routes_session.py` — session_snapshot ZIP + report endpoints

### Pipeline package (api/pipeline/)
- `orchestrator.py` — main pipeline driver (_explore_worker), all phase functions
- `types.py` — ExploreContext + ExploreRuntime dataclasses
- `helpers.py` — shared helpers, constants, write policy precheck
- `vocab.py` — vocabulary table management, hypothesis, schema backfill
- `prompts.py` — LLM prompt builders, synthesis, behavioral spec generation
- `checkpoint.py` — checkpoint save/load/seed/merge system

### Stage directories (api/pipeline/s{NN}_{name}/)
Each stage has: `__init__.py` (context docs + re-exports), `CONTEXT.md`, stage modules.
- `s00_setup/` — sentinel calibration, vocab seed, static analysis
- `s01_unlock/` — write-unlock probe, XOR code generation
- `s02_probe/` — curriculum ordering, per-function LLM probe loop
- `s03_reconcile/` — reconciliation, MC-3 write analysis, sentinel catalog
- `s04_synthesis/` — API reference synthesis, MC-4 init clues
- `s05_enrichment/` — schema backfill, verification, MC-5 chaining
- `s06_gaps/` — gap resolution, MC-6 final unlock
- `s07_finalize/` — behavioral spec, harmonization, contract artifacts

### Legacy shims (api/explore*.py)
The old flat files are now thin shims that re-export from api/pipeline/*.
They exist for backward compatibility only. Always import from api.pipeline.*.

## Code Style
- Never use cryptic abbreviations (_wuo, _hc, _pv, etc.)
- Never alias imports to shorter names (_JOB_INVOCABLE_MAPS as _jimap)
- Exception variable names: always `exc`, not `_wue`, `_rle`, `_fb_e`
- Use `snake_case` for all variables and functions
- Comments explain WHY, not WHAT

## Pipeline Architecture
The explore pipeline has 11 phases (0-10) plus 4 micro coordinator checkpoints.

### Stage and Phase Naming Convention

Every pipeline step has a canonical identifier: `S-{stage}.{substep}`

| ID | Function | Stage Name | Package |
|----|----------|------------|---------|
| S-00.1 | `_run_phase_05_calibrate` | Sentinel calibration | s00_setup |
| S-00.2 | `_run_phase_0_vocab_seed` | Vocab seed | s00_setup |
| S-00.3 | `_run_phase_0_static` | Static analysis | s00_setup |
| S-01.1 | `_run_phase_1_write_unlock` | Write-unlock probe | s01_unlock |
| S-02.1 | `_run_phase_2_curriculum_order` | Curriculum ordering | s02_probe |
| S-02.2 | `_run_phase_3_probe_loop` | **Probe loop (main work)** | s02_probe |
| S-03.1 | `_run_phase_4_reconcile` | Reconcile probe log | s03_reconcile |
| S-03.MC | `_mc3_post_reconcile` | **MC: write failure analysis** | s03_reconcile |
| S-03.2 | `_run_phase_5_sentinel_catalog` | Sentinel catalog | s03_reconcile |
| S-04.1 | `_run_phase_6_synthesize` | Synthesis (api-reference.md) | s04_synthesis |
| S-04.MC | `_mc4_post_synthesis` | **MC: parse synthesis for init clues** | s04_synthesis |
| S-05.1 | `_run_phase_7_backfill` | Schema enrichment | s05_enrichment |
| S-05.2 | `_run_phase_7b_verify_enrichment` | Verification (execute working_calls) | s05_enrichment |
| S-05.MC | `_mc5_post_verification` | **MC: chain read -> write** | s05_enrichment |
| S-06.1 | `_run_phase_8_gap_resolution` | Gap resolution | s06_gaps |
| S-06.MC | `_mc6_post_gap_resolution` | **MC: final comprehensive unlock** | s06_gaps |
| S-07.1 | `_run_phase_9_behavioral_spec` | Behavioral spec | s07_finalize |
| S-07.2 | `_run_phase_10_harmonize` | Harmonize | s07_finalize |
| S-07.3 | Finalize | Contract artifacts (T-01 through T-21) | s07_finalize |

### Checkpoint System (api/pipeline/checkpoint.py)
- Saves per-stage and per-function checkpoint data to blob storage
- `checkpoint_id` in explore_settings loads a prior checkpoint
- `focus_functions` limits probing to specific functions only
- `skip_to_stage` resumes from a stage boundary
- Checkpoints are saved after each stage completes
- Functions with status="success" and working_call are skippable

### Micro Coordinators:
Each MC reads what the previous phase produced, reasons about it, adjusts strategy,
and documents its decision in `{job_id}/mc-decisions/mc{N}-*.json`.

- MC-3 (S-03.MC): classifies write failure mode (uniform sentinel = init problem vs mixed)
- MC-4 (S-04.MC): parses synthesis doc for init mode patterns
- MC-5 (S-05.MC): chains verified read outputs as concrete write args
- MC-6 (S-06.MC): final comprehensive attempt with all accumulated knowledge

When any MC cracks write-unlock, it immediately re-probes all failed write functions
and persists the winning init sequence to `winning_init_sequence.json`.

### Transitions:
- T-01..T-16: Original cohesion data flow transitions
- T-17: sentinel_calibration_outcome (Q16)
- T-18: write_unlock_probe_outcome (Q16)
- T-19: mc_coordinator_decisions (MC-3 through MC-6 artifact presence)
- T-20: enrichment_verification_outcome (Phase 7b verified/inferred/error counts)
- T-21: winning_init_sequence_persistence (write-unlock crack persisted for future runs)

### Circular Feedback:
Pass `prior_job_id` in explore_settings to seed from a previous session.
Loads: findings, sentinel table, vocab, api-reference.

### Write functions:
ProcessPayment, ProcessRefund, RedeemLoyaltyPoints, UnlockAccount
(matched by _WRITE_FN_RE in api/pipeline/helpers.py)
Write functions get 14 tool calls (not 8) and targeted init->write testing prompts.

## Testing
- 21 transitions in transition-index.json (T-01 through T-21)
- Tests parse routes_session.py (not main.py) for ZIP structure
- Run: pytest tests/ -v --tb=short --ignore=tests/test_mcp_stdio.py
- Circular test: scripts/run_circular_test.py (3-iteration cold->warm->hot)

## Key Files for Context Strategies
- `api/pipeline/s02_probe/probe_loop.py` — LLM prompt and per-function agent loop
- `api/pipeline/prompts.py` — system message builders
- `api/pipeline/s06_gaps/gap_resolution.py` — gap resolution second-pass probing
- `api/pipeline/checkpoint.py` — checkpoint system for resumable focused runs
- `docs/architecture/COLLECTIVE-ARCHITECTURE.md` — macro/micro coordinator design
- `docs/architecture/PIPELINE-PARAMETERS.md` — all configurable parameters
- `docs/architecture/PIPELINE-RESTRUCTURE-PLAN.md` — restructure plan

## Azure / Cost
- Container Apps: min-replicas 0 (scale to zero when idle)
- VM: deallocate when not testing
- All CI/CD workflows use min-replicas 0
